==Leeds 399== 
[[Image:OldTram 700.jpg|right|170px]]
Leeds 399 was built at Leeds Kirkstall Works, and entered service in 1925.<ref name=Official_fleetlist>{{cite web|url=http://www.tramway.co.uk/smx/cms/tramfleet2/|title=Official Fleetlist}}</ref>

This tramcar was the second one to arrive at Crich, however it faced a lengthy restoration, returning only to service in 1991.<ref name=Guidebook-2003-2008>{{cite book|title=Crich Tramway Village Guidebook, 2003-2008 Edition|date=2003-2008|publisher=National Tramway Museum}}</ref> It is now one of the most used cars at Crich, and is in the Winter Operating Fleet.<ref name=BTO_fleetlist>{{cite web|url=http://www.britishtramsonline.co.uk/crich.html|title=British Trams Online Fleetlist}}</ref>
